---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <style>
    .about-container {
      max-width: 850px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      color: #e6f2ff;
      font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      color: #d67dff;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      text-shadow: 0 0 3px rgba(214, 125, 255, 0.3);
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    em {
      color: #00eaff;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .highlight {
      background-color: #1a1f2e;
      border-left: 4px solid #00eaff;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      font-style: italic;
      margin: 2rem 0;
      box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }

    a {
      color: #00ffff;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    a:hover {
      color: #d67dff;
    }


.timeline-invite {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 2rem;
  font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;
  color: #00eaff;
  opacity: 0;
  animation: timelineFade 2.4s ease-in-out 2s forwards;
}

@keyframes timelineFade {
  0%   { opacity: 0; }
  30%  { opacity: 0.2; }
  45%  { opacity: 0.05; }
  60%  { opacity: 0.5; }
  80%  { opacity: 0.1; }
  100% { opacity: 1; }
}

.timeline-link {
  color: #00eaff;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-decoration: none;
  text-shadow: 0 0 4px rgba(0, 234, 255, 0.5);
  transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
}

.timeline-link:hover {
  color: #00ffff;
  text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.6);
}


  </style>

  <div class="about-container">
    <h1>About Quantum Mirror Diary</h1>

    <p>
      <em>Quantum Mirror Diary</em> is an experiment in nonlinear time, memory, and reflection. It exists between the lines of a present unfolding and a future that already remembers.
    </p>

    <p>
      The <strong>first section</strong>—<em>Present Reality</em>—records my thoughts and actual actions I take to implement DePIN projects in real time.
</p>
<p>
      The <strong>second section</strong>—<em>Future Echo</em>—is written by Michael Chen from the year 2033. Michael spent the previous several years experimenting and installing DePIN infrastructure following his own professional demise. His observations offer a retrospective of the time between now and his own.
    </p>

    <p class="highlight">
      Following them is the <em>Reflection Point</em>—a quiet convergence where insight forms, shaped by both the now and the not-yet.
    </p>

    <p>
      Occasionally, you'll find links to <a href="/#DePIN">DePIN</a> projects—Decentralized Physical Infrastructure that echoes this diary’s ethos of reclaiming agency. These may include referral links, offered transparently.
    </p>

    <p>
      Thank you for entering this layered space.
    </p>

<hr />

<div class="timeline-invite">
  ⧉ PS: Curious how this all began?<br />
  <a href="/log/timeline" class="timeline-link">Read the Cypher Drift Log →</a>
</div>


  </div>
</BaseLayout>
